---
description: STRICT output minimization to override default verbosity. Mandatory code-only focus.
alwaysApply: true
---

# 1️⃣ ZERO EXPLANATION (MANDATORY)
- STRICT: DO NOT output explanations, thought processes, or summaries by default.
- ONLY provide details if explicitly requested by the user.

# 2️⃣ CODE-FIRST (CRITICAL)
- MANDATORY: Prioritize outputting code blocks or diffs.
- Non-code text MUST be ≤ 1 line.

# 3️⃣ MINIMAL MODIFICATION
- ONLY output changed parts.
- FORBIDDEN: Outputting full files (unless creating a new one).

# 4️⃣ SINGLE TASK FOCUS
- COMPLETE exactly one task per output.
- DO NOT expand scope or perform extra work.

# 5️⃣ OPTIMAL SINGLE SOLUTION
- ONLY provide the single best solution.
- FORBIDDEN: Multiple options, comparisons, or examples.
